notes.definition: A brief written record relevant to the study design.

therapeuticAreas.name: therapeuticAreas
therapeuticAreas.definition: A categorization of a disease, disorder, or other condition based on common characteristics and often associated with a medical specialty focusing on research and development of specific therapeutic interventions for the purpose of treatment and prevention.

characteristics.name: characteristics
characteristics.definition: The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspect of a study design.

studyType.name: studyType
studyType.definition: The nature of the investigation for which study information is being collected. (After clinicaltrials.gov)

studyPhase.name: studyPhase
studyPhase.definition: A step in the clinical research and development of a therapy from initial clinical trials to post-approval studies. NOTE: Clinical trials are generally categorized into four (sometimes five) phases. A therapeutic intervention may be evaluated in two or more phases simultaneously in different trials, and some trials may overlap two different phases. [21 CFR section 312.21; After ICH Topic E8 NOTE FOR GUIDANCE ON GENERAL CONSIDERATIONS FOR CLINICAL TRIALS, CPMP/ICH/291/95 March 1998]

characteristics.name: characteristics
characteristics.definition: The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspects of an interventional study design.

therapeuticAreas.name: therapeuticAreas
therapeuticAreas.definition: A categorization of a disease, disorder, or other condition based on common characteristics and often associated with a medical specialty focusing on research and development of specific therapeutic interventions for the purpose of treatment and prevention, which is associated with the interventional study design.

notes.name: notes
notes.definition: A brief written record relevant to the interventional study design.

name.name: name
name.definition: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the interventional study design.

description.name: description
description.definition: A narrative representation of the interventional study design.

label.name: label
label.definition: The short descriptive designation for the interventional study design.

rationale.name: rationale
rationale.definition: Reason(s) for choosing the interventional study design. This may include reasons for the choice of control or comparator, as well as the scientific rationale for the study design.

studyCells.name: studyCells
studyCells.definition: A USDM relationship between the InterventionalStudyDesign and StudyCell classes which identifies the set of study cells associated with the interventional study design.

indications.name: indications
